      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the iconic S54B32 inline-six engine. This high-revving power plant utilizes individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver a linear power band up to its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory limited-slip differential. The chassis has received critical preventative maintenance, including rear subframe reinforcement and a VANOS system refresh to ensure structural and mechanical integrity. The suspension retains its factory-spec geometry, providing the communicative steering and lateral stability characteristic of the M-division's engineering. While the aesthetic reflects its status as a well-loved driver, the powertrain remains tight and responsive.",
